direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods involve manipulating the DOM structure by either wrapping elements with HTML or unwrapping them, making them complementary in functionality.
Both methods modify the DOM structure by either removing child nodes (unwrap) or emptying the content of elements (empty).
Both methods involve removing elements from the DOM, though unwrap moves children to their parents while remove completely removes the elements.
The unwrap method operates on selected elements, making it dependent on the select method for identifying which elements to unwrap.
The unwrap method may indirectly depend on the parse method from QueryParser for selecting elements based on complex queries.
